body:
Been working on this for several months now, but I finally managed to get PyTorch master to build on Blue Waters! Of course, you have to disable most of the variants, as the system CUDA is no longer supported by PyTorch and many other dependencies can't be built with such an old GLIBC.

@maxim-belkin 

Successfully builds on Cray CNL5 (SUSE 11) with Python 3.8.11 and GCC 8.2.0.
